This Chassis actually beds the rifle for accuracy, no further bedding required. Just torque the attachment screws to spec.  I do have the take off overmolded stock for this rifle.  

The optic is a Nikon Monarch (top of the Nikon line) 4-14X44mm Mil-dot Reticle, sunshade (30 bucks extra), and I have purchased the target turrets for more easy dialing if needed (70 bucks extra) I do have the original box and turrets for this optic. This is a new optic, no scratches, or marks. Adjustable side parallax (focus). You can use this optic with Nikons "Spot-On" software on their website to dial in a specific data card for your specific load. A very helpful software if you do not currently have a ballistic program. 

I am currently looking to trade for a nice AR10 bull barrel for my GF to hog/deer hunt with. Cash talks as well.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield SAR-8 (HK-91 by Helenic Arms, Greece)
postcontent: This is a Springfield SAR-8 sporter made in Greece. This is not to be confused with the newer (and vastly inferior) SAR-8 sold by Springfield with the cast aluminum receiver, this is all steel receiver, and not some parts kit build. These are HK-91 clones made on HK tooling set-up by HK engineers, made by HK trained technicians at Hellenic Arms. These were imported by Springfield as SAR-3 for a while before being caught up in the early assault weapon ban. Springfield slapped a thumb hole stock on them, pinned and welded a non flash suppressor on them and overstamped the SAR-3 with an SAR-8. The quality on these is felt to be second only to HK since everything was set-up by them. Included are 3x 20rd steel magazines, 5x 20 rd aluminum magazines, and the original 5 rd magazine. This rifle does have some small handling marks but I would say it is still in very good condition. It has been kept in a safe and very well taken care of. I'm parting with it because my interests have changed and I need to make room for some other projects. TX drivers license and bill of sale required for transaction, prefer CHL. If you have any questions, please send them and I will respond promptly. I'm also interested in trades (AKs, ARs, tactical rifles, tactical shotguns, historical firearms, really want a LaRue or Noveske upper).  I will be in Tyler, TX the Dec 21-25 and the DFW area Jan 1.

title: For Sale:  7.62x54r 180 gr heavy ball
postcontent:
For sale is some VERY nice 7.62x54r, made in Hungary in 1988.  This is 180 grain silver/yellow tip heavy ball ammunition, with a steel core projectile.  Steel case, and appears to be polymer coated instead of the normal green laquer coating (Laquer causes sticky bolt syndrome).  Corrosive, so clean appropriately.
$8 per 20-rd box

This is rare ammunition - heavy ball is no longer produced for this caliber.  I've shot this and the 1970's Russian and Bulgarian light ball, and this Hungarian heavy ball has groups half the size of the light ball.  It is very accurate, consistent, and has superb long range ballistics. 
Get it while you can.

This example dates to 1944. All the parts are stamped by their individual makers and are proper for a weapon produced by Winchester in 1944. Includes 150 rounds of ammo.
